lator function only; assert merged string excludes banned snippet; catches local merge bug; misses leakage from fixture injector. Current(Integration, chosen): run real harness assembly path with fixtures; assert final prompt has no copied phase instructions; catches cross-module interpolation/fixture leakage; misses live model-side effects. High(System): run full CLI/subprocess harness; catches process/env wiring bugs; misses little extra for this specific artifact check. Lowest sufficient: Current Integration.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The test invocation loads skill context from plugin/skill files and validates behavior from that context rather than from hard-coded prompt rules.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core failure is wiring: invocation must source context from plugin/skill files and not embedded constants (module interaction + filesystem inputs). Integration brake: (a) can be reproduced with local temp skill files in-process; no real network/subprocess needed. (b) this behavior can be validated by source-of-truth swapping/inspection without depending on model quality. (c) no multi-agentic chain. Rejected Agentic because behavior text emphasizes \"loads skill context...rather than hard-coded prompt rules\" (proven by controlled context-source tests).","test_description":"Candidates: Low(Unit): test one loader function returns file content; catches parse/path bug; misses invocation path still using hard-coded rules. Current(Integration, chosen): run invocation through real harness with two skill-file variants and unchanged prompt; assert loaded context fingerprint in assembled request and hard-coded fallback absent; catches bypass/hard-code regressions; misses model-quality regressions. High(Agentic): also assert output behavior shift with live model; catches semantic steering failures; unnecessary for proving context source in this behavior. Lowest sufficient: Current Integration.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.3,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The harness can run the same user-style prompt against an intentionally degraded or missing SKILL.md variant without changing test prompt text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is harness configurability and data injection across modules/files. Integration brake: (a) no real external infra needed; local file variants suffice. (b) no dependence on AI output correctness for this capability check. (c) no multiple agentic steps. Rejected System because behavior text is about harness ability to \"run...against variant\" not OS-level phenomena.","test_description":"Candidates: Low(Unit): test config resolver picks variant path; catches selector bug; misses end-to-end invocation usage. Current(Integration, chosen): execute harness twice (baseline vs degraded/missing skill), same prompt text; assert run config switches skill source only and invocation proceeds; catches hidden prompt mutation/hard-coded fallback. High(Agentic): require output difference from live model too; catches semantic impact but exceeds this behavior’s capability requirement. Lowest sufficient: Current Integration.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the relevant SKILL.md section is removed or degraded, the behavioral test fails under the same user-style prompt.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real model behavior changing when skill guidance degrades (LLM-DEP true; deterministic stubs hide exactly this regression). Not Workflow: single model decision path is enough; behavior text specifies one prompt/run condition, not multi-agent pipeline. Rejected Integration because it would only verify plumbing, not whether degraded skill context actually causes behavioral failure.","test_description":"Candidates: Low(Integration): stub model output and assert fail on degraded skill flag; catches harness branch bug; misses real model insensitivity to skill regression. Current(Agentic, chosen): run same prompt live with baseline vs degraded skill section; assert structural/behavioral expectation passes baseline and fails degraded; catches true semantic-regression masking. High(Workflow): multi-step planner->critic pipeline with repeated calls; catches compounded orchestration failures; disqualified because behavior text is single behavioral test under same prompt. Lowest sufficient: Current Agentic.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.12}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Raw model output is captured to a diagnostic artifact before any JSON parsing or extraction logic runs.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is ordering across modules: model client -> artifact writer -> parser/extractor. Needs wiring test, not model-quality test. Integration brake: (a) local filesystem artifact is enough; no real network/OS primitive beyond normal file I/O. (b) no dependence on model semantic correctness. (c) no multi-agentic chain. Rejected System because subprocess/real network behavior is not part of stated failure.","test_description":"Candidates: Low(Unit): test helper that writes artifact; catches serializer bug; misses call-order regression. Current(Integration, chosen): instrument harness with fake model response, run pipeline, assert artifact exists with raw payload before parser is invoked (e.g., parser forced to throw yet artifact persists); catches pre-parse capture ordering bug. High(System): run full CLI process and inspect on-disk artifacts; catches process-level path/env issues; unnecessary for core ordering behavior. Lowest sufficient: Current Integration.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Assertions enforce structural behavior constraints (for example schema paths and role-specific field placement), not only keyword presence checks.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Primary failure boundary is assertion logic design (predicate semantics on structured output). MOCK-MISS: no required cross-module interaction to catch keyword-vs-structure weakness. REAL-INFRA/LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none required. Rejected Integration because behavior text targets assertion rule content itself, which can be validated with crafted fixtures.","test_description":"Candidates: Low(Unit): feed one malformed fixture with right keywords but wrong field placement; assert failure; catches keyword-only trap; misses broader schema variants. Current(Unit, chosen): table-driven fixtures (correct, keyword-only false positive, wrong role path, missing nested field); assert structure rules pass/fail appropriately; catches weak assertion definitions. High(Integration): include parser+assertion together; catches parser-contract mismatches; not required to prove structural-vs-keyword enforcement. Lowest sufficient: Current Unit.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.6,"Integration":0.32,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"Under live model execution, structural assertions catch regressions that a keyword-only check would miss.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires \"live model execution\" and regression detection based on actual model outputs; mocked outputs can always be shaped to pass and hide real drift (LLM-DEP true). Not Workflow: single live generation evaluated by two assertion styles; no required multi-step agent chain. Rejected Integration due explicit behavior text requiring live model path.","test_description":"Candidates: Low(Integration): replay canned outputs and compare keyword vs structural assertions; catches assertion implementation bugs; misses real-model regression patterns. Current(Agentic, chosen): run live prompt suite, store raw outputs, evaluate both assertion sets; assert at least one case where keyword passes but structural fails on regression; catches real semantic/format drift. High(Workflow): multi-turn agent pipeline with planner/tool/critic and cross-step structural checks; catches chained decision failures; disqualified because behavior is single live execution check. Lowest sufficient: Current Agentic.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.76,"Workflow":0.15}}]}
